The South African Reserve Bank
plans to sell 600 million rand ($80.9 million) of inflation-
linked bonds maturing in 2022, 2028 and 2033.  The auction is at 11 a.m. in  Pretoria , with the results
announced about 30 minutes later.  To contact the reporter on this story:
